Governor Ahmadu Fintiri has  received donation of N200 million and three bus ambulances from  BUA Group of Companies as support in the  fight against COVID-19 in Adamawa State Alhaji Abdulsamad Rabiu, represented by a former Minister of State for Health, Dr Idi Hong, said the gesture was to support the state to curb the spread of coronavirus. Dr Hong said BUA Group Foundation had so far spent about N7 billion assisting governments and corporate organizations across the country and stressed that the company will continue to render assistance towards development of humanity. Responding after receiving documents of the vehicles and a dummy check for the N200 million, Governor Umaru Fintiri expressed appreciation to the Chairman of the BUA Group for the donation at a time when the economy is in serious crisis. The Governor promised that government will use the vehicles and the money donated for the purpose intended, declaring that the N200 million had already been deposited at the state COVID-19 Containment account. He also revealed that government had been receiving donations from the citizens in the state since the outbreak of coronavirus in Adamawa and called on other philanthropic organizations to emulate the gesture of BUA Group in assisting governments to fight the virus. 